Windows Registry Demystified

What is the Windows Registry, and what does it store?

The Windows Registry is a hierarchical database used by the Microsoft Windows operating system to store configuration settings and options. It serves as a central repository for information about the software and hardware installed on a Windows system, as well as user preferences and system settings. 

What are the two types of registry settings stored for each Windows user account?
HKEY_CURRENT_USER (HKCU) and HKEY_USERS (HKU)


